
[1]gravity

   GRAV'ITY, n. [L. gravitas, from gravis, heavy. See Grave.]

   1. Weight; heaviness.

   2. In philosophy, that force by which bodies tend or are pressed or
   drawn towards the center of the earth, or towards some other center, or
   the effect of that force; in which last sense gravity is synonymous
   with weight.
